1/17/2023 14:59:53,Koronesuki,"Currently, my is biggest obsession in life is learning Japanese, a goal which I have been working hard towards on the side of my studies at KTH for about a year and a half. It has lead me to take a large interest in the culture as well, with everything from the food and folk customs to anime and Vtubers.

I also enjoy training, especially jogging. I believe that one should work on both the body and the mind in order to realize ones true capabilities (studies have also shown that mental capacity increases if one trains). Thus, I'm currently doing a mix of strength training, jogging, flexibility and handstand practice in order to make sure I stay in shape.

I've always had a fondness for video games as well. In fact, they are what lead me to have an interest in pursuing programming and visualisation here at KTH. Thus, the side of visualization/graphics that I am the most interested in is computer graphics, but I'm hoping that this course will be a lot of fun as well!

I've been trying to get into the artistic side of things too recently. I'm mostly doing 3D modeling but I've dabbled in drawing as well. I thought it might be a good idea to be able to mix the more scientific side of visualisation and graphics that I expect to get from KTH with a more artistic side that I can develop on my own. I'm still at the beginning of that journey though.",2,2,5,4,8,5,1,3,2,5,4,5

I'm mostly very uninterested in sports though I love scuba diving, if that can really be considered a sport.
